      <critique id="A6" status="done">
        <creator agent="true" created="2025-12-14T16:43:43.542Z" agent-type="critique"/>
        <ref ref="/world/characters/Remedy.card#v4.0.0"/>
        <ref ref="/stories/Mandatory_Assistance/chapters/5_Settling_In/passages/3_Preparation/passage.card#v3.0.0"/>
        <feedback>
          MISSED OPPORTUNITY: Remedy's 'unsettling decomposition comments' flaw underutilized in farewell scene.

          In Preparation (lines 108-121), Remedy appears for a final wound check before Kira's departure: 'Perfectly healed! Full regeneration, excellent structural integrity. You won't decompose from this injury!' Kira: 'Thanks, Remedy. Your chemistry saved my life.' Remedy: 'Chemistry is what chemistry does... Travel safely. Come back and tell me about the other territories' decomposition patterns. I'm curious.'

          The character card (line 37-38) explicitly states as a flaw: 'Proud of decomposition abilities but doesn't realize how unsettling it is to casually mention being able to break down Kira's dead body very efficiently.'

          This farewell scene was a PERFECT opportunity for Remedy to say something accidentally disturbing about decomposition (like 'If you die in another territory, their decomposers will process you differently than I would - less efficient!' or 'Travel safely! Though if you don't, at least you'll become excellent soil somewhere!'). 

          The character card's humor style (lines 60-68) includes examples like: 'You're approximately 60% water, 20% protein, 15% fat, 5% minerals. Very decomposable. I mean, not that we want to! But chemically speaking, you'd break down beautifully.'

          Instead, Remedy's dialogue is surprisingly tactful and appropriate. This undermines the established character trait of being casually morbid without realizing it. The flaw should manifest MORE in emotional moments (farewells, caring interactions) because that's when Remedy would naturally express care through their decomposition-focused lens, not less.
        </feedback>
        <reason>Made farewell more accidentally morbid - added body processing time and nitrogen cycle concerns</reason>
